(107, '24', 'What are the indications for Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid is indicated for treating infections caused by sensitive bacteria, including:\r\n\r\nPharyngitis/Tonsillitis caused by Streptococcus pyogenes.\r\nAcute Bacterial Otitis Media caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae, Haemophilus influenzae, and Moraxella catarrhalis.\r\nAcute Bacterial Maxillary Sinusitis caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae or Haemophilus influenzae.\r\nLower Respiratory Tract Infections (including pneumonia) caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae, Haemophilus influenzae, Klebsiella spp., and Staphylococcus aureus.\r\nAcute Bacterial Exacerbation of Chronic Bronchitis and secondary infections of acute bronchitis caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae, Haemophilus influenzae, or Haemophilus parainfluenzae.\r\nUncomplicated skin and skin structure infections caused by Staphylococcus aureus or Streptococcus pyogenes.\r\nUncomplicated Urinary Tract Infections caused by E. coli or Klebsiella pneumoniae.\r\nBone and Joint Infections caused by Staphylococcus aureus.\r\nUncomplicated Gonorrhea caused by Neisseria gonorrhoeae.\r\nEarly Lyme Disease caused by Borrelia burgdorferi.\r\nSepticemia caused by various bacteria like Staphylococcus aureus and E. coli.\r\nMeningitis caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae, Neisseria meningitidis, and Staphylococcus aureus.\r\nSwitch therapy from injectable to oral for certain infections.', 'what-are-the-indications-for-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:47:04', '2024-10-08 16:47:04'),
(108, '25', 'What is the pharmacological action of Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime is a second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic that works by inhibiting bacterial cell wall synthesis, leading to cell death. Clavulanic acid is a beta-lactamase inhibitor that binds irreversibly to beta-lactamase enzymes, preventing the degradation of cefuroxime by beta-lactamase-producing bacteria, thereby enhancing its efficacy against resistant bacteria.', 'what-is-the-pharmacological-action-of-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:47:30', '2024-10-08 16:47:30'),
(109, '24', 'What is the pharmacological action of Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime is a second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic that works by inhibiting bacterial cell wall synthesis, leading to cell death. Clavulanic acid is a beta-lactamase inhibitor that binds irreversibly to beta-lactamase enzymes, preventing the degradation of cefuroxime by beta-lactamase-producing bacteria, thereby enhancing its efficacy against resistant bacteria.', 'what-is-the-pharmacological-action-of-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:47:33', '2024-10-08 16:47:33'),
(110, '24', 'What is the recommended dosage for Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Adults (13 years and older):\r\n\r\nPharyngitis/Tonsillitis: 250 mg twice daily for 5-10 days.\r\nAcute Bacterial Maxillary Sinusitis: 250 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nAcute Exacerbation of Chronic Bronchitis: 250-500 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nUncomplicated Skin Infections: 250-500 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nUncomplicated Urinary Tract Infections: 250 mg twice daily for 7-10 days.\r\nGonorrhea: 1000 mg as a single dose.\r\nPneumonia: 250-500 mg twice daily for 5-10 days.\r\nEarly Lyme Disease: 500 mg twice daily for 20 days.\r\nPediatric Patients (3 months to 12 years):\r\n\r\nPharyngitis/Tonsillitis: 20 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 5-10 days.\r\nAcute Otitis Media and Sinusitis: 30 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 10 days.\r\nImpetigo: 30 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 10 days.', 'what-is-the-recommended-dosage-for-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:48:04', '2024-10-08 16:48:04'),
(111, '25', 'What is the recommended dosage for Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Adults (13 years and older):\r\n\r\nPharyngitis/Tonsillitis: 250 mg twice daily for 5-10 days.\r\nAcute Bacterial Maxillary Sinusitis: 250 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nAcute Exacerbation of Chronic Bronchitis: 250-500 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nUncomplicated Skin Infections: 250-500 mg twice daily for 10 days.\r\nUncomplicated Urinary Tract Infections: 250 mg twice daily for 7-10 days.\r\nGonorrhea: 1000 mg as a single dose.\r\nPneumonia: 250-500 mg twice daily for 5-10 days.\r\nEarly Lyme Disease: 500 mg twice daily for 20 days.\r\nPediatric Patients (3 months to 12 years):\r\n\r\nPharyngitis/Tonsillitis: 20 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 5-10 days.\r\nAcute Otitis Media and Sinusitis: 30 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 10 days.\r\nImpetigo: 30 mg/kg/day in two divided doses for 10 days.', 'what-is-the-recommended-dosage-for-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:48:09', '2024-10-08 16:48:09'),
(112, '24', 'Are there any drug interactions with Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid?', 'Probenecid increases serum concentrations of cefuroxime by 50%.\r\nDrugs that reduce gastric acidity may lower cefuroxime\'s bioavailability, negating the effects of postprandial absorption.', 'are-there-any-drug-interactions-with-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:48:33', '2024-10-08 16:48:33'),
(113, '25', 'Are there any drug interactions with Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid?', 'Probenecid increases serum concentrations of cefuroxime by 50%.\r\nDrugs that reduce gastric acidity may lower cefuroxime\'s bioavailability, negating the effects of postprandial absorption.', 'are-there-any-drug-interactions-with-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:48:37', '2024-10-08 16:48:37'),
(114, '25', 'What are the contraindications for Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid is contraindicated in patients with:\r\n\r\nKnown allergy to cephalosporins.\r\nPseudomembranous colitis.', 'what-are-the-contraindications-for-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:48:59', '2024-10-08 16:48:59'),
(115, '24', 'What are the contraindications for Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid is contraindicated in patients with:\r\n\r\nKnown allergy to cephalosporins.\r\nPseudomembranous colitis.', 'what-are-the-contraindications-for-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:49:02', '2024-10-08 16:49:02'),
(116, '25', 'What side effects may occur with Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Common side effects include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain. Rarely, renal dysfunction, anaphylaxis, angioedema, rash, and serum sickness-like reactions may occur.', 'what-side-effects-may-occur-with-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:49:23', '2024-10-08 16:49:23'),
(117, '24', 'What side effects may occur with Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Common side effects include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain. Rarely, renal dysfunction, anaphylaxis, angioedema, rash, and serum sickness-like reactions may occur.', 'what-side-effects-may-occur-with-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:49:26', '2024-10-08 16:49:26'),
(118, '25', 'Can Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus) be used during pregnancy and lactation?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid can be used during pregnancy, especially in the later stages, but should be avoided in the first trimester if possible. It is excreted in small amounts into breast milk, so caution should be exercised, considering the possibility of sensitizing the infant.', 'can-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus-be-used-during-pregnancy-and-lactation', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:49:49', '2024-10-08 16:49:49'),
(119, '24', 'Can Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus) be used during pregnancy and lactation?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid can be used during pregnancy, especially in the later stages, but should be avoided in the first trimester if possible. It is excreted in small amounts into breast milk, so caution should be exercised, considering the possibility of sensitizing the infant.', 'can-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus-be-used-during-pregnancy-and-lactation', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:49:51', '2024-10-08 16:49:51'),
(120, '25', 'What precautions should be taken while using Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'It should be used cautiously in patients receiving potent diuretics or with a history of colitis. Care should be taken in patients with renal dysfunction, as dosage adjustment may be required.', 'what-precautions-should-be-taken-while-using-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:50:17', '2024-10-08 16:50:17'),
(121, '24', 'What precautions should be taken while using Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'It should be used cautiously in patients receiving potent diuretics or with a history of colitis. Care should be taken in patients with renal dysfunction, as dosage adjustment may be required.', 'what-precautions-should-be-taken-while-using-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:50:21', '2024-10-08 16:50:21'),
(122, '25', 'What is the therapeutic class of Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid belongs to the second-generation cephalosporins therapeutic class, known for their broad-spectrum activity against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.', 'what-is-the-therapeutic-class-of-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:50:42', '2024-10-08 16:50:42'),
(123, '24', 'What is the therapeutic class of Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid (Furotil Plus)?', 'Cefuroxime-Clavulanic Acid belongs to the second-generation cephalosporins therapeutic class, known for their broad-spectrum activity against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.', 'what-is-the-therapeutic-class-of-cefuroxime-clavulanic-acid-furotil-plus', NULL, '2024-10-08 16:50:45', '2024-10-08 16:50:45'),
