(43, 'hpl', NULL, 'about', 'Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Ltd. (HPL) is one of the leading pharmaceutical companies in Bangladesh, certified by international pharmaceutical regulatory authorities such as TGA (Australia), NPRA (Malaysia), MCAZ (Zimbabwe), TFDA (Tanzania), and others.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">HPL focuses on innovation and delivers healthcare solutions that improve and extend people&rsquo;s lives. From prevention to treatment, HPL transforms scientific innovation into healthcare solutions in areas such as Antihistamines, Antiemetics, Anti-diabetics, Analgesics and Antipyretics, Anti-infectives, Bone Care, Biotech and Oncology, CNS Drugs, Cardiovascular, Dermatological Products, Respiratory Care, Ophthalmics, Vitamins &amp; Minerals, and many more. Healthcare Pharmaceuticals Ltd. began its journey in 1988 by establishing Healthcare Distribution Limited in association with Roche Limited, a renowned Switzerland-based multinational company. Until 2001, HPL was responsible for importing and distributing Roche products to the local market. In 1996, HPL decided to establish its own pharmaceutical plant to produce products that were being imported from Roche, Switzerland, as well as other local generics for the domestic market. Today, Healthcare Pharmaceuticals is the fastest-growing organization in Bangladesh&#39;s pharmaceutical industry. We are currently producing over Four hundred products in various dosage forms, including Tablets, Capsules, Liquids, Dry Syrups, Creams &amp; Ointments, Gels, Small Volume Parenterals, and Eye Drops, covering almost all therapeutic classes. Numerous products are also in the pipeline for launch in both local and international markets across Asia, Africa, and the CIS region.</p>', '', '2024-09-23 10:59:00', '2024-10-01 09:28:12'),
